{"title_page": "2008 Wichita State Shockers baseball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college baseball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| sport = baseball\n| year = 2008\n| team = Wichita State Shockers\n| logo = Wichita State Shockers baseball logo.svg\n| logo_size = 150\n| logo_alt = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| conference = Missouri Valley Conference\n| short_conf = Missouri Valley\n| CoachRank = 13\n| CBRank = 12\n| record = 48-17\n| conf_record = 19-5\n| head_coach = [[Gene Stephenson]]\n| hc_year = 31st\n| asst_coach1 = Bret Kemnitz\n| ac1_year = \n| asst_coach2 = Jim Thomas\n| ac2_year = \n| asst_coach3 = \n| ac3_year = \n| mvp =\n| mvp_year =\n| captain =\n| captain_year =\n| captain2 =\n| captain2_year =\n| stadium = [[Eck Stadium]]\n| champion = [[Missouri Valley Conference|MVC champion]]<br>[[2008 Missouri Vally Conference Baseball Tournament|MVC Tournament champion]]\n| tourney =[[2008 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]\n| tourney_result = [[2008 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament#Tallahassee Super Regional|Super Regional]]\n}}\n{{2008 Missouri Valley Conference baseball standings}}\nThe '''2008 Wichita State Shockers baseball team''' represented [[Wichita State University]] in the [[2008 NCAA Division I baseball season]]. The Shockers played their home games at [[Eck Stadium]] under 31st year coach [[Gene Stephenson]].\n\n==Previous Season==\nThe 2007 Wichita State Shockers baseball team finished the year 53-22 overall and 20\u20134 in the Missouri Valley Conference. The Shockers had their own [[2007 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament#Wichita Super Regional|Super Regional]]. In the first game, Wichita State would lose 6\u20137 to [[New Orleans Privateers baseball|New Orleans]]. In the losers' bracket they would beat Oral Roberts 11\u20134, a rematch win against New Orleans 7\u20133, and would beat [[Arizona Wildcats baseball|Arizona]] in the next two games 4-3 then 3\u20130 in the Regional Finals. In the Super Regionals, the Shockers would lose to [[UC Irvine Anteaters baseball|UC Irvine]] 0-1 then 2\u20133.\n\n===2007 MLB Draft===\nThe Shockers had ten players drafted in the [[2007 MLB draft]].<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/draft/?key_school=b6ff1406&exact=1&query_type=key_school</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"65%\"\n|- align=\"center\" \n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Wichita State Shockers|Player|Position|Round|Overall|MLB Team}} \n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[Pete Kozma]]* || Shortstop || 1 || 18 || [[St. Louis Cardinals]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| Jon Gilmore* || Infield/Pitcher || 1-s || 33 || [[Atlanta Braves]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[Derek Norris]]* || Catcher || 4 || 130 || [[Washington Nationals]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| Travis Banwart || Pitcher || 4 || 150 || [[Oakland Athletics]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| Damon Sublett || Second baseman || 7 || 244 || [[New York Yankees]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| Matt Brown || Outfield || 13 || 407 || [[Cleveland Indians]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| Noah Krol || Pitcher || 17 || 541 || [[Detroit Tigers]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| '''Josh Workman''' || Second baseman || 23 || 722 || [[Minnesota Twins]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| '''Kenneth Williams''' || Outfield || 32 || 971 || [[Colorado Rockies]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| Kyle Touchatt || Pitcher || 34 || 1026 || [[Baltimore Orioles]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| '''Tyler Fleming''' || Pitcher || 39 || 1179 || [[Texas Rangers]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| Ronnie Morales || Pitcher || 45 || 1342 || [[Chicago White Sox]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| '''Nick Cobler''' || Pitcher || 49 || 1431 || Minnesota Twins\n|}\n{{clear}}\n* Peter Kozma was expected to play for Wichita State, but was drafted and signed with the St. Louis Cardinals.<ref>https://goshockers.com/news/2006/11/16/691530.aspx</ref>\n* Jon Gilmore was expected to play for Wichita State, but was drafted and signed with the Atlanta Braves.\n* Derek Norris was expected to play for Wichita State, but was drafted and signed with the Washington Nationals.\n\nPlayers in '''bold''' are signees drafted from high school, community colleges that will attend Wichita State or attendees that will stay for the 2008 season.\n\n==Roster==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"text-align: left; font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"9\" style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Wichita State Shockers}}; text-align:center;\"| 2008 Wichita State roster\n|-\n|width=\"03\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n'''[[Pitcher]]s'''\n*3 Logan Hoch - ''Junior''\n*4 Tyler Fleming - ''Junior''\n*15 Cameron Maldonado - ''Freshman''\n*21 Matt Smith - ''Junior''\n*23 Clint Maune - ''Freshman''\n*26 Any Womack - ''Senior''\n*27 Tyson Fugett -''Sophomore''\n*29 Rob Musgrave - ''Senior''\n*32 Max Huston - ''Senior''\n*35 Anthony Capra - ''Junior''\n*36 Tim Kelley - ''RS Freshman''\n*41 Aaron Shafer - ''Junior''\n*42 Khol Nanney - ''RS Senior''\n\n\n|width=\"15\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n'''[[Catcher]]s'''\n*12 Tyler Weber - ''Senior''\n\n'''[[Infielder]]s'''\n*1 Kyle Sisney - ''RS Freshman''\n*7 Taylor Brown - ''Freshman''\n*19 Roberto Rios - ''Junior''\n*22 Josh Workman - ''RS Junior''\n*34 [[Conor Gillaspie]] - ''Junior''\n\n\n|width=\"15\"|&nbsp;\n| valign=\"top\" |\n'''[[Outfielder]]s'''\n*2 Bret Bascue - ''RS Sophomore''\n*9 [[Andy Dirks]] - ''Senior''\n*11 [[Kenny Williams (baseball)#Personal life|Kenny Williams Jr]]. - ''RS Junior''\n*13 Ryan Jones - ''Sophomore''\n*18 Kevin Hall - ''Freshman''\n\n'''[[Utility player#Baseball|Utility]]'''\n*6 Remington Johnson (1B/P) - ''Freshman''\n*8 Dusty Coleman (INF/P) - ''Sophomore''\n*14 Ryan Engrav (UTIL) - ''Freshman''\n*16 Grant Muncrief (3B/P) - ''Freshman''\n*17 Justin Kemp (C/P) - ''Freshman''\n*20 Mitch Caster (OF/P) - ''Freshman''\n*31 Clint McKeever (1B/P) - ''RS Sophomore''\n*33 Cody Lassley (UTIL) - ''RS Sophomore''