h1 = Bret Kemnitz\n| ac1_year = \n| asst_coach2 = Jim Thomas\n| ac2_year = \n| asst_coach3 = \n| ac3_year = \n| mvp =\n| mvp_year =\n| captain =\n| captain_year =\n| captain2 =\n| captain2_year =\n| stadium = [[Eck Stadium]]\n| champion = [[Missouri Valley Conference|MVC champion]]<br>[[2008 Missouri Vally Conference Baseball Tournament|MVC Tournament champion]]\n| tourney =[[2008 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]\n| tourney_result = [[2008 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament#Tallahassee Super Regional|Super Regional]]\n}}\n{{2008 Missouri Valley Conference baseball standings}}\nThe '''2008 Wichita State Shockers baseball team''' represented [[Wichita State University]] in the [[2008 NCAA Division I baseball season]]. The Shockers played their home games at [[Eck Stadium]] under 31st year coach [[Gene Stephenson]].\n\n==Previous Season==\nThe 2007 Wichita State Shockers baseball team finished the year 53-22 overall and 20-4 in the Missouri Valley Conference. The Shockers had their own [[2007 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament#Wichita Super Regional|Super Regional]]. In the first game, Wichita State would lose 6-7 to [[New Orleans Privateers baseball|New Orleans]]. In the losers' bracket they would beat Oral Roberts 11-4, a rematch win against New Orleans 7-3, and would beat [[Arizona Wildcats baseball|Arizona]] in the next two games 4-3 then 3-0 in the Regional Finals. In the Super Regionals, the Shockers would lose to [[UC Irvine Anteaters baseball|UC Irvine]] 0-1 then 2-3.\n\n===2007 MLB Draft===\nThe Shockers had ten players drafted in the [[2007 MLB draft]].<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/draft/?key_school=b6ff1406&exact=1&query_type=key_school</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"65%\"\n|- align=\"center\" \n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Wichita State Shockers|Player|Position|Round|Overall|MLB Team}} \n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"\"\n| [[Pete Kozma]]* || Shortstop || 1 || 18 || [[St. Louis Cardinals]]\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=